    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available is a driver-focused 2005 Porsche 911 Carrera (997.1) featuring the naturally aspirated 3.6L flat-six powerplant mated to a precise 6-speed manual transaxle. This example is mechanically robust, boasting a documented IMS bearing retrofit and a recently replaced clutch assembly with a dual-mass flywheel. The PASM-equipped suspension provides exceptional damping control, while the chassis remains taut with refreshed control arm bushings for sharp turn-in. The engine exhibits strong compression across all cylinders and a clean bore-scope inspection. While the exterior shows honest road-derived patina, the drivetrain and hydraulic steering rack offer a visceral, communicative experience that remains true to the 911 legacy.",
      "price": 34500.0,
      "reputation": 0.4,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 35
    },
    {
